  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A comprehensive UQ campaign was conducted covering Latin hypercube sampling across 12 geometric and boundary-condition parameters; one-at-a-time sensitivity sweeps were embedded within the validation study and are documented in the validation result narratives. Structured sensitivity analysis linkage follows standard MRL 2 reporting practice.",
