      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Richardson extrapolation applied across three systematically refined meshes (3.2M, 12.8M, 51.2M elements). Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI: 2.1% on fine mesh. Asymptotic range confirmed (ratio 1.97 vs theoretical 2.0). Discretization uncertainty propagated into total model uncertainty budget.",
      "passFail": "Pass",
      "quantitativeMetric": "GCI_fine = 2.1%; observed order p = 1.97"
