    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Hemolysis prediction NRMSE of 7.3% satisfies acceptance criterion. Mesh convergence GCI of 2.1% demonstrates adequate discretization control. UQ campaign (LHS n=128, 12 parameters) documented in TR-2024-07 confirms model outputs are robust to input uncertainty across COU operating envelope. Six not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1. Overall credibility evidence supports use of CFD model to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for Class II CPB device regulatory submission.",
